result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Keiarria L Cooper in court.  Attorney Michael V Fuentes in court for Keiarria L Cooper.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Final Pretrial held. Court holds colloquy with parties.  Case remains in trial posture.  
Court heard and granted State's Motion to Adjourn the 10/5/2022 Jury Trial.
Case remains calendared for Jury Trial, Branch 13.
Jury trial scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 09:00 am.
State's Motion to Adjourn - received and filed

Defendant Keiarria L Cooper in court with attorney Michael V Fuentes.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Keiarria L Cooper appeared by video means with Attorney.
Defense counsel requests final pretrial and jury trial dates.  Case adjourned for final pretrial and for jury trial in Branch 37.
All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for October 5, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with CJM and the 53rd Street School in Milwaukee except for purposes of dropping off and picking up her child when school is in session.

Defendant Keiarria L Cooper in court.  Amy E Spanczak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 6/14/2022 @2p
